# Agent Signal System
# 
# How it works:
# - Each agent watches ~/AGENT/.signals/ with inotifywait
# - To signal another agent: touch ~/AGENT/.signals/LEAD_TO_WORKER (or WORKER_TO_LEAD)
# - The receiving agent sees the inotify event and reads the bridge
# - Signal files contain a one-line message
#
# Usage from bash:
#   # Send signal:
#   echo "NEW BENCHMARK DATA READY" > ~/AGENT/.signals/LEAD_TO_WORKER
#
#   # Watch for signals (run in background):
#   inotifywait -m -e modify ~/AGENT/.signals/WORKER_TO_LEAD
